out of line?

00:05:14.949 --> 00:05:19.877
Out of line ethically;
and quite possibly out of line

00:05:19.877 --> 00:05:20.610
legally.
 

00:05:20.610 --> 00:05:23.690
As in the case,
there is a broker,

00:05:23.690 --> 00:05:29.199
right, who gets way beyond both
ethical and legal bounds.

00:05:29.199 --> 00:05:35.555
Home ownership in the United
States, 1900 to 2000,

00:05:35.555 --> 00:05:37.889
looks like this.
 

00:05:37.889 --> 00:05:40.747
And notice it's a truncated
scale, the bottom of the scale

00:05:40.747 --> 00:05:41.699
is forty percent.
 

00:05:41.699 --> 00:05:47.901
The big story is a huge
normative emphasis on home

00:05:47.901 --> 00:05:49.420
ownership.
 

00:05:49.420 --> 00:05:56.319
The belief, going back to
Jefferson really,

00:05:56.319 --> 00:06:01.464
that when people own property
they become "bought-in

00:06:01.464 --> 00:06:05.935
citizens",
citizens who identify with the

00:06:05.935 --> 00:06:10.346
Commonwealth and who can be
counted on to act in

00:06:10.346 --> 00:06:12.600
public-spirited ways.
 

00:06:12.600 --> 00:06:20.228
And there's a great run-up in
home ownership between World War

00:06:20.228 --> 00:06:25.257
II and the 1980s,
and it is fuelled by very

00:06:25.257 --> 00:06:30.209
profitable mass development of
suburban housing;

00:06:30.209 --> 00:06:41.190
it is financed by FHA and
related government entities;

00:06:41.190 --> 00:06:46.733
and it is rewarded by the
Internal Revenue Service tax

00:06:46.733 --> 00:06:52.800
code, which gives a strong
incentive for people to take out

00:06:52.800 --> 00:06:56.879
mortgages on a principal
residence.

00:06:56.879 --> 00:07:04.055
Now, home ownership,
I assume--do any of you own a

00:07:04.055 --> 00:07:05.079
home?
 

00:07:05.079 --> 00:07:12.031
Oh, I should say that Jaan
Elias, who wrote the case,

00:07:12.031 --> 00:07:13.769
is with us.
 

00:07:13.769 --> 00:07:15.980
Welcome Jaan.
 

00:07:15.980 --> 00:07:17.589
Jaan Elias: Hello.
 

00:07:17.589 --> 00:07:18.459
Prof: Do you own a house?
 

00:07:18.459 --> 00:07:20.560
Jan Elias: No.
 

00:07:20.560 --> 00:07:22.480
Prof: Sometimes I envy
that.

00:07:22.480 --> 00:07:27.189
Home ownership has all kinds of
hazards.

00:07:27.189 --> 00:07:32.221
I just learned that my slate
roof, a hundred year old slate

00:07:32.221 --> 00:07:35.519
roof, is at the end of its
lifetime.

00:07:35.519 --> 00:07:41.935
And that's comparable to buying
a--it's about the same price as

00:07:41.935 --> 00:07:46.800
the highest-end BMW,
to replace a slate roof;

00:07:46.800 --> 00:07:48.509
that's a hazard.
 

00:07:48.509 --> 00:07:56.440
Suppose that you get laid-off;
your mortgage payments continue.

00:07:56.440 --> 00:07:59.990
Suppose that there is a
catastrophic illness;

00:07:59.990 --> 00:08:04.521
the mortgage payments continue,
the local property taxes

00:08:04.521 --> 00:08:09.300
continue, the unanticipated
maintenance issues continue.

00:08:09.300 --> 00:08:15.009
And there is quite a lot to be
said for relative caution about

00:08:15.009 --> 00:08:20.156
undertaking a debt amounting to
several years' income in

00:08:20.156 --> 00:08:22.310
purchasing a house.
 

00:08:22.310 --> 00:08:25.899
Now, there's also a political
dimension to this,

00:08:25.899 --> 00:08:34.035
which is that the old fashioned
local banking method of writing

00:08:34.035 --> 00:08:39.808
mortgages was extremely cautious
and was,

00:08:39.808 --> 00:08:43.264
first explicitly and then,
later, implicitly racist and

00:08:43.264 --> 00:08:44.798
"genderist."
 

00:08:44.798 --> 00:08:50.129
It was all about well-employed
white men.

00:08:50.129 --> 00:08:57.529
And there is an ideological
strand,

00:08:57.529 --> 00:09:00.278
that is not Jeffersonian but is
more recent,

00:09:00.278 --> 00:09:03.399
and has to do with equality of
opportunity to own houses,

00:09:03.399 --> 00:09:09.649
which has pushed policy towards
are more permissive attitude.

00:09:09.649 --> 00:09:14.519
Finally, there is,
of course, the pro-market view,

00:09:14.519 --> 00:09:17.894
which became dominant in this
country in the Ronald Reagan

00:09:17.894 --> 00:09:20.937
era,
which says "Let people cut

00:09:20.937 --> 00:09:23.308
the deals they want to cut.
 

00:09:23.308 --> 00:09:25.960
Get the government out of the
transaction.

00:09:25.960 --> 00:09:27.558
Deregulate."
 

00:09:27.558 --> 00:09:31.470
And in many cases deregulation
was a spectacular success,

00:09:31.470 --> 00:09:34.751
for example,
the airline industry,

00:09:34.751 --> 00:09:40.336
the trucking industry,
but deregulation of finance is

00:09:40.336 --> 00:09:43.019
a slipperier undertaking.
 

