00:10:36.308 --> 00:10:44.250
In 1937 mortgages were
collapsing all over the country.

00:10:44.250 --> 00:10:47.774
And the Roosevelt
Administration pushed through

00:10:47.774 --> 00:10:52.216
Congress a piece of legislation
called The Home Owners Loan

00:10:52.216 --> 00:10:55.355
Corporation,
HOLC, Home Owners Loan

00:10:55.355 --> 00:10:56.440
Corporation.
 

00:10:56.440 --> 00:10:59.808
And the Home Owners Loan
Corporation was charged with

00:10:59.808 --> 00:11:03.243
finding out how to know in
advance if a mortgage would

00:11:03.243 --> 00:11:04.278
likely fail.
 

00:11:04.278 --> 00:11:10.633
And the technique was not to
look at credit scores but to

00:11:10.633 --> 00:11:17.299
look at housing locations;
and to look at the condition of

00:11:17.299 --> 00:11:22.669
housing in a neighborhood;
and at the demographics of who

00:11:22.669 --> 00:11:23.678
lived there.
 

00:11:23.678 --> 00:11:29.721
And it was crudely racist and
biased in many,

00:11:29.721 --> 00:11:31.370
many ways.
 

00:11:31.370 --> 00:11:35.990
It was explicitly racist about
blacks;

00:11:35.990 --> 00:11:39.860
it was explicitly racist about
Jews;

00:11:39.860 --> 00:11:44.398
it was explicitly racist about
Italians, most of all Southern

00:11:44.398 --> 00:11:45.230
Italians.
 

00:11:45.230 --> 00:11:52.075
And it was a four-point scale,
the worst category - level D -

00:11:52.075 --> 00:11:54.052
was red,
and the term

00:11:54.052 --> 00:11:56.460
"redlining"
comes from this,

00:11:56.460 --> 00:12:00.349
and the idea was to tell the
banking world not to lend money

00:12:00.349 --> 00:12:01.470
in those zones.
 

00:12:01.470 --> 00:12:07.460
Yellow was a little better,
then blue,

00:12:07.460 --> 00:12:14.580
then green and the idea was to
put mortgage money into the

00:12:14.580 --> 00:12:18.205
safest,
wealthiest neighborhoods with

00:12:18.205 --> 00:12:20.990
the most homogeneous
populations.

00:12:20.990 --> 00:12:27.076
And from the point of view of
managing the mortgage crisis,

00:12:27.076 --> 00:12:30.330
it was not a terrible policy.
 

00:12:30.330 --> 00:12:35.538
From the point of view of
managing cities and communities,

00:12:35.538 --> 00:12:40.376
it was catastrophic because
what it did was to accelerate

00:12:40.376 --> 00:12:45.041
the creation of slums in areas
where mortgage money was

00:12:45.041 --> 00:12:49.620
unavailable for the sale or
purchase of housing,

00:12:49.620 --> 00:12:52.932
or, for that matter,
for the large-scale repair of

00:12:52.932 --> 00:12:53.610
housing.
 

00:12:53.610 --> 00:12:57.690
They did it to two
hundred--they did the process to

00:12:57.690 --> 00:13:02.423
two hundred American cities in a
single year, including New

00:13:02.423 --> 00:13:03.240
Haven.
 

00:13:03.240 --> 00:13:06.450
Across Chapel Street is class D.
 

